    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would a client bug be able to create more supply? Multiple clients would certainly help in some way though.\r\n\r\nRegardless, the question was more about why _shouldn't_ a validator exploit a bug? If they have no liability as a validator and can guarantee that they'll have a position as a attester or valitdator during some slot, what is there against them from doing that? Nakamoto Consensus relies more on \"you shouldnt\" than \"you'll get punished\" and it certainly stood the test of time so far.",
